@brotherjord Dear Jordan, hello. Thank you for contacting us. You can check your SKYPASS number as follows.

ㅇOnline member : Log in https://t.co/mprUVQk6bi &gt; Find ID &gt; Find SKYPASS No.

ㅇNon Online member :  Sign up https://t.co/mprUVQk6bi &gt; I have a SKYPASS number &gt; Find SKYPASS No.

@manchestair Dear @manchestair , hello. Thank you for contacting us.

In-flight safety card is very important asset which provides passengers' safety guideline in emergency, so the card should not be removed from aircraft.

Kindly understand that we are not able to accept your request.

@kluszaksosmin Dear Michael, hello. Thank you for asking.

As you can see on our website, here's the example of 48 hours/2 days rule : If taking flights to Korea at 19:00 on Jan 22, 2022, documents tested after 0:00 on Jan 20, 2022 will be accepted.

Your case seems to meet that restriction.

@monique2IV Dear Monique, hello. Thank you for choosing Korean Air. 

If your ticket from Savannah to Atlanta(or other departing US city) and then to Incheon is in one reservation number, your free baggage allowance will be 2 bags, 23kg or less each.

https://t.co/OJ3EOOnD0v

@cloudifythings Dear @cloudifythingsa , hello. Thank you for asking. You can easily search Estimated Time of Arrival(ETA) by typing a flight number on google.
(example : https://t.co/zWuXHprlrW )

It seems like the flight is already arrived Jakarta.
